{"title_page": "Pymmes Brook Trail", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2015}}\n[[File:Pymmes Park Trail.JPG|thumbnail|Pymmes Brook Trail sign]]\nThe '''Pymmes Brook Trail''' is located in the London Boroughs of [[London Borough of Barnet|Barnet]], [[London Borough of Enfield|Enfield]] and [[London Borough of Haringey|Haringey]] and is just under {{convert|13|miles|km}} long. The brook is named after [[William Pymme]], a local landowner.\n\nThe trail goes from [[Monken Hadley Common|Hadley Green]] to [[Tottenham Hale]], where the trail connects with the [[Lea Valley Walk]]. Most of the first half of the trail, as far as [[Arnos Park]], runs beside  [[Pymmes Brook]], but after that the brook is only encountered intermittently as much of the brook passes through private land which is not open to the public. In its lower reaches sections of the brook have been [[culvert]]ed to alleviate the risk of flooding.<ref>[http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk/static/documents/Research/summary_ll_1459052.pdf Environment Agency] {{webarchive|url=http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20110203031308/http%3A//www.environment%2Dagency.gov.uk/static/documents/Research/summary_ll_1459052.pdf |date=3 February 2011 }} Retrieved 18 January 2011</ref>\n\n== Course ==\nThe trail starts on [[Hadley Green]], where the headwaters of Pymmes Brook rise, with a link from [[High Barnet tube station]].  Together with the [[London Loop]], it then drops through [[Monken Hadley Common]] to [[Charles_Jack#Death_and_legacy|Jack's Lake]], to meet another link from [[Cockfosters tube station]].  Pymmes Brook proper starts here as it flows out from Jack's Lake.  The trail detours through [[Victoria Recreation Ground, New Barnet|Victoria Recreation Ground]], where Pymmes Brook is joined with [[Shirebourne brook]], then follows a short street section to rejoin the brook at [[East Barnet|East Barnet Village]].  It then runs beside the brook through [[Oak Hill Park (Barnet)|Oak Hill Park]] and [[Brunswick Park]] to the halfway point in [[Arnos_Grove#Arnos_Park|Arnos Park]], with a link to [[Arnos Grove tube station]]. It is also where Pymmes Brook is joined by Bounds Green Brook. The trail then leaves the brook to pass through [[Broomfield Park, Palmers Green|Broomfield Park]] and [[Palmers Green]]. It crosses over the [[New River (London)|New River]] at Oakthorpe Road, then the [[A406 road|North Circular Road]], to divert through two new public open spaces - Bowes Meadow and Tile Kiln Lane Open Space - where Pymmes Brook can be followed again. The trail recrosses the North Circular Road onto Silver Street, [[Edmonton, London|Edmonton]], where the path enters the gardens of [[Millfield House]]. From here the trail leads to [[Pymmes Park]] and another brookside section, then to Fore Street, where the brook flows underground to merge with [[Salmons Brook]] to the south of [[Angel Road]]. As of 2018, the trail must temporarily follow public throughfares for a short distance, but will eventually take a new route when access to the brook is opened up in the [[Meridian Water]] development.  Finally, the trail passes through [[Tottenham Marshes]], beside Pymmes Brook and past [[Stonebridge Lock]] on the [[Lee Navigation]], to reach the point where the brook joins the [[River Lea]]. The trail connects with the [[Lea Valley Walk]] at [[Tottenham Lock]], with a link to [[Tottenham Hale station]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Pymmes Brook Trail |url=https://www.ldwa.org.uk/ldp/members/show_path.php?path_name=Pymmes+Brook+Trail |website=The Long Distance Walkers Association |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery perrow=\"6\">\nFile:Pymmes Brook Trail, Jacks Lake.JPG|<!-- Beech Hill Lake, I used to live on Beech Hill, but I only know the \"lake\" as -->Jack's Lake on Monken Hadley Common\nFile:Pymmes Brook in Arnos Park.JPG|Pymmes Brook in Arnos Park\nFile:Pymmes Brook Trail, Broomfield Park lake.JPG|Broomfield Park lake\n